{"_id":"55a5295c-97bd-3885-8f6d-3511c66d1e26","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"You should be using asynchronous I/O for all your network communications. This is good advice in general, but especially if you have scaling concerns.  \r\n\r\nIf you have control over the protocol, then impose some kind of message framing on the xml messages. It's possible to detect xml messages without explicit message framing, but it's quite complicated (and inefficient).","postId":"2009_04_sample-code-length-prefix-message-ba45f669-db06-32ff-ba50-472b420edace","replyTo":"","date":"2012-10-19T00:33:39Z","timestamp":1350606819,"authorUserId":""}